               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Words yǝbelu (ʾaḫaw) and yǝbe (mätärgwǝm) introducing each question and answer; incipit of chapters two and four on fols. 19ra and 31ra, respectively; a few other words introducing a section (e.g., fols. 54vb, 65ra); elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
A few lines on the incipit page of the text.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The text consists of a series of questions asked by monks (beginning with ይቤሉ: አኃው) and answers given by an “interpreter” (starting with ይቤ: መተርጕም). The questions are numbered.</note>
                     <note>- Traces of the original division of the text into ክፍል “part” on fols. 19rb (“chapter two”) and 31rb (“chapter four”).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
